While coding an app, we have to make keep in mind some design principles. We have to make sure the users are able to manipulate the screen directly this enhances the understanding and engages the the user. We should be able to acknowledge feedback actions so we know how the user is feeling about using the app. Also we have to make sure the user is able physically interact with the screen in form of click and drag, toggle switches, move sliders etc this helps the user learn more quickly. Finally we have to make sure the user is in control of the app, not the other way around. We can guide the user on what is a desirable action but ultimately the decision should be the Users\'92.\
