App Store Review Guidelines \
Basically the review process is where Apple deems your app to be fit to be showcased in their App Store available to millions of users worldwide. They pride themselves in providing a safe environment for kids. They want to make sure the app you submit is an app that is an app that adheres to the not only legal guidelines but also moral guidelines. The submitted app should be accepting of differing opinions and not crossing a line. Also the no type of cheating should take place whether it be trying to get by the review process, stealing user data manipulating ratings or app discover otherwise they will remove the app and yourself from their developer program. The App Review process is there to prevent not only any faulty apps to make their way on to the appstore but to also prevent apps that might not be socially acceptable or may cause harm.\
